channel.title: Hello, I'm Tofpu! :)
channel.description: Recent content on Hello, I'm Tofpu! :)

item.description: About Introduction Hello there, I’m referred to as “Tofpu” in the internet realm. I’m a programmer whose specializes in Minecraft Development; precisely the server-side of things. I have been developing server-side plugins for over two years and I strive to build the highest-quality plugins possible for my clients. I have published some of my work over at GitHub & Spigot, feel free to check out the projects tab for more information.

Projects Public Projects: SpeedBridge MemorizeTheBlock LockedDimension MobPreventer SpeedBridge A practicing-based plugin where you hop into an island, bridge from one island to another, and get the lowest score possible. MemorizeTheBlock A memory-based plugin where you hop into the game and memorize the three blocks in front of you in a span of seconds, and then place the blocks as you have remembered them in their oriented spot. LockedDimension Allows you to disable, lock dimensions behind permissions nodes, and much more.
